$ Azure Active Directory

Azure Active Directory is sometimes abbreviated with *Azure AD*.

Among others(?), Azure Active Directory allows to authorize access rights to secured resources through Azure role-based access control (Azure RBAC).

sa:

  The Azure Services
    • Azure Active Directory Domain Services
    • Azure Active Directory B2C
    • Azure Directory External Identities
  See also → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/az/ResourceProvider/get[`get-azResourceProvider`]

  There is a N:1 relationship between *Azure subscription* and *Azure Active Directory*: a subscription trusts *one* Azure AD to authenticate users, services and devices. (But one Azure AD might
  authenticate multiple subscriptions).

  *Resource Providers* for Azure Active Directory include
    • Microsoft.ADHybridHealthService
    • Microsoft.Compute
